T1  - Stochastic dominance and portfolio analysis
AU  - Ali, Mukhtar M.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 2
IS  - 2
SP  - 205
EP  - 229
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/06/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(75)90005-7
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X75900057
AB  - The principle of stochastic dominance is used to characterize the optimal efficient sets when the distributions of the random prospects belong to a family. Most of the well-known distributions are considered. In each case, the optimal efficient sets are characterized by easily verifiable conditions on the parameters of the distributions. These optimal efficient sets are then compared with the corresponding mean-variance (MV) efficient set. It is often found that the optimal efficient sets are proper subsets of the MV efficient set. Thus, the MV criterion is a proper efficiency criterion, but the MV efficient set can be excessively large compared to the optimal efficient set.
